## Summary

### вң… DO

- Query only tables from your bounded context in repositories
- Create application services to orchestrate multiple repositories
- Return only IDs from junction tables in repositories
- Use events for eventual consistency when appropriate
- Make cross-context dependencies explicit at service layer
- Test repositories and services independently

### вқҢ DON'T DO

- Don't query tables from other bounded contexts in repositories
- Don't use Prisma `include` to join cross-context tables
- Don't validate entities from other contexts in repositories
- Don't return DTOs with cross-context data from repositories
- Don't hide cross-context dependencies in repository methods
- Don't skip the service layer for cross-context orchestration
